title: [BUG] Error 400 when submitting two equal zips in the same dataset
body:
The identified bug was:
1. Uploading files with the same name would not always result in files being renamed.
2. Additional zip uploads would "reupload" whatever was already in the user's temp dir. 

Before approving this PR, I would recommend you to try uploading whatever zip file you can find that has uvl files, preferably with several directories.
Closes #83

title: [BUG] Clicking on a tag does not filter results by it
body:
**Describe the bug**
In the Explore page, when you click on a tag, it is supposed to filter search results by it. However, since the introduction of the search queries WI (#8), this has not been the case.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Go to Explore.
2. Click on the tag of a dataset.
3. Unless the tag string matches with the title of another dataset, no results will be found.

**Expected behavior**
The Explore tab should only show results with the tag that was clicked on.

**Screenshots**
![Screenshot from 2024-12-15 14-36-24](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b9b76483-b2e5-40d0-9120-cf36e39bfe90)
![Screenshot from 2024-12-15 14-36-15](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/96d7811a-ec76-41aa-9822-899140f17421)

**Additional context**
It is still possible to filter datasets by tags by tiping "tags: [tag]" in the search bar.

title: [BUG] Error 500 when submitting an empty rating
body:
**Describe the bug**
When a rating is submitted without any stars, the website shows error 500. Looking at the exception raised, it seems like the rating service is trying to perform a query to add a rating, but it fails since `value` is an incorrect integer (null). 

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Log in as you would do normally.
2. Find a dataset to rate.
3. Click on Ratings.
4. Without adding a rating or a comment, click on Submit Rating.
5. A screen with 500 Internal Server Error will appear.

**Expected behavior**
There should be a step in the validation where `value` is checked to ensure that it is not null and between 1 and 5. If it is not, the user should see an error message that reads something like "Please give the dataset a rating between 1 and 5 stars."

Edit: typo
